cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CC, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the problem of inter-datacenter virtual machine migration with network capacity constraints, which involves network infrastructure and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on datacenters and energy consumption, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The proposed algorithms involve optimization and decision-making, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions simulations and algorithms, which could relate to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
